"Have you hugged your druid today?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uicknay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Icknay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 5:41:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Triggered Faydedar...</span><hr size=1> I can add some info, here.  I've been killed by the triggered Fay probably 6 times now and every time he as stomped around our corpses until he poofed.  He never ever leaves the hidden oasis.  I've seen him poof in 15 minutes or so...and I've seen him take OVER 2 hours to poof.  Saturday we did him...well, he did us...and he took almost 3 full hours to poof.  Most people had to log to stop the rez clock.  One of my guildies said she was on a Fay raid a couple of months ago and he was up for 4+ hours after wiping them out.  I missed that raid somehow, thank goodness.  <br>
One more thought...if a pedestrian or wandering player goes inside the hidden oasis while Fay is still up that player is going to die.  Maybe that activity resets the poof clock?  Just a thought...that would explain how his poof time differs so much.<br>
Icknay<br>
54th Druid<br>
Blood and Honor<br>
Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhanahthedruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hanah the Druid</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 6:05:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Triggered Faydedar...</span><hr size=1> Icknay, we need to get him killed for you :)  right after we get him killed for me :p<br>
<br>
Hanah, the Druid Goddess <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caraddor>Caraddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 6:27:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Triggered Faydedar...</span><hr size=1> Hmm.. When we did Faydedar for my epic, the spawn wasn't instantaneous.  I set everyone up and handed in the essence.  Nothing happend (I had thought it would be instant).  I stood there for a couple seconds, then hit track.  Faydedar was on track.  I closed the track window and headed back to my group, and that's when I was hit by the first AE fear wave (resisted, but at least I knew he was coming then ;) ).  <br>
<br>
So, if you hand it in and nothing happens instantly, check your track window.  Faydedar may have a cup of tea before charging your force :)<br>
<br>
There is no other loot on the triggered Faydedar.  Only one pod of seawater will drop.  Does anyone know if the regular Faydedar still drops the water?  I don't think I've seen that question answered yet.  I'm assuming it doesn't.<br>
<br>
I've not been on any failed Faydedar kills (many thanks to those that posted strategies here.. they worked great), so I wouldn't know first hand about despawning.  If you put together a capable force (one that could take down Ragefire or Nagafen), you shouldn't have to worry about the failure part.<br>
<br>
Caraddor (Order of the Scattered Winds)<br>
52 Wanderer<br>
Bertoxx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 7:22:07 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Triggered Faydedar...</span><hr size=1> Yes, the real Fay does drop the pod of water. I helped kill him for some friends, and a 60 druid got the pod (I didn't roll, it was their guild's kill). He also dropped a shield and a couple of other things. Don't remember exactly what, though. <br>
<br>
I believe the triggered Fay spawns immediately, but doesn't come up out of the water for a few seconds. Perhaps he spawns way in the back, and it takes a few seconds for him to attain aggro, and rush the players. <br>
<br>
I kill him this Saturday for my final piece. I'll make sure to check track right after giving the essense to see if he spawned.  <p><a href="mailto:Cuchulaine@luclin.com">Cuchulaine Kynthelig</a> <BR>
